    "a-abstract": {
      "type": "elementBody",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "When a system generates thousands of unique outputs from a set of authored rules, who is the designer? This paper explores the nature of authorship in constraint-based and generative practice — from Vera Molnár's early computer drawings through contemporary parametric systems — and asks where craft and intention still locate themselves when the output is unexpected.",
